Vice President Kamala Harris had a conversation with President Tshisekedi of the Democratic Republic of the Congo. They discussed various topics including COVID-19, recent Ebola outbreaks, and economic opportunities. They expressed their commitment to strengthening health security, promoting regional trade and investment, and addressing climate change. The Vice President also pledged to work with the DRC government to improve girls' education and economic opportunities for all Congolese. Additionally, they discussed the concerns of the United States regarding human rights violations and a humanitarian crisis in the Tigray region of Ethiopia. They agreed to collaborate in reducing conflict, supporting dialogue, and securing peace in eastern DRC and the region.